summary: TL* THE CONTACT OWNED A 2004 HONDA ACCORD. WHILE DRIVING 45 MPH, THE CONTACT'S VEHICLE WAS INVOLVED IN A CRASH. THE CONTACT ATTEMPTED TO STOP THE VEHICLE FROM STRIKING AN OBJECT IN THE ROAD AND CRASHED INTO THE MEDIAN. THE AIR BAGS DID NOT DEPLOY. A POLICE REPORT WAS NOT FIELD. THE CONTACT SUSTAINED INJURIES TO THE BACK AND CHEST, WHICH REQUIRED MEDICAL ATTENTION. THE VEHICLE WAS DESTROYED AND TOWED. THE DEALER AND MANUFACTURER WERE NOT CONTACTED. THE VIN AND FAILURE MILEAGE WERE UNKNOWN.
